com.worldpay

Class SaveCardActivity

  • java.lang.Object
    • Activity
      • com.worldpay.SaveCardActivity

  • public class SaveCardActivity
extends Activity
    An activity that shows a dialog to add card details and creates a transaction.

    The form contains information for :

    • First name
    • Last name
    • Card Number
    • Expire date (month/year)
    • CVC

    Usage

    1. Declare the activity in AndroidManifest.xml 
             <activity android:name="com.worldpay.SaveCardActivity"   android:label="Card Details" />
    2. Open the activity : 
       
 Intent intent = new Intent(myactivity, SaveCardActivity.class);
 // SAVE_CARD_REQUEST_CODE a custom request code for that activity
 startActivityForResult(intent, SAVE_CARD_REQUEST_CODE);
    3. Handle activity response implementing Activity#onActivityResult

      The developer uses Intent parameter from Activity#onActivityResult to retrieve more information about the result.

    Theme Customisation

    The developer can choose a theme by passing a bundle property to the intent. The property name is EXTRA_CUSTOMIZE_THEME and a colour int needs to be passed. 
     
 intent.putExtra(SaveCardActivity.EXTRA_CUSTOMIZE_THEME,
                Color.parseColor("#ff0000"));

    Results

    The activity returns the results with a result code and as extras into the Intent parameter of onActivityResult.
    Possible results :
    • RESULT_RESPONSE_CARD :
      The activity had a successful transaction and returns result of a ResponseCard.
      It can be accessed with a statement: 
       
 ResponseCard responseCard = (ResponseCard) data
                .getSerializableExtra(SaveCardActivity.EXTRA_RESPONSE_CARD);
    • RESULT_RESPONSE_ERROR :
      An error occured, the activity returns details in a ResponseError object.
       
 ResponseError responseCardError = (ResponseError) data
                .getSerializableExtra(SaveCardActivity.EXTRA_RESPONSE_ERROR);
    • RESULT_WORLDPAY_ERROR :
      Generic Worldpay error, details can be found in a WorldpayError: 
       
 WorldpayError worldpayError = (WorldpayError) data
                .getSerializableExtra(SaveCardActivity.EXTRA_RESPONSE_WORLDPAY_ERROR);
